@namespace TheCanalaveLibrary.SharedUI

@* Cross-cutting layout element — injected into MainLayout before
   <LoginDisplay/>. Spec §cross-cutting.md "Notification Bell".

   Injection-free wrapper: the real content + @inject services live in NotificationBellInner,
   instantiated only when AuthorizeView renders Authorized — deferring DI resolution and the
   notification fetch until we actually know the viewer is authenticated. See
   layer3-logic.md "Deferring DI Behind AuthorizeView (WU43)" — @inject on THIS component (or,
   as NotificationBell originally had it, written physically inside <Authorized> markup) would
   still resolve and this component's own OnInitializedAsync would still run at construction
   time regardless of the AuthorizeView decision. That gap is what let an anonymous WASM render
   (e.g. the moment right after logout) call the real RequireAuthorization() endpoint and throw
   an unhandled 401 into the shared "chrome" error boundary — the server impl tolerated it
   (anonymous-safe zero/empty return), which is why it went unnoticed until the WASM client path
   went live.

   Interaction pattern: UserCard caret (relative + toggle button → absolute top-full panel),
   NOT the fixed inset-0 modal pattern. See layer3.5-structure.md "NotificationBell". *@

<AuthorizeView>
    <Authorized>
        <NotificationBellInner />
    </Authorized>
</AuthorizeView>
